http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Release-honorarium-for-guest-lecturers%E2%80%99/article13994862.ece

Guest Lecturers working in government degree colleges have urged the State government to release their honorarium, which is pending for over three months.In a memorandum submitted to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, they said that around 14,000 guest lecturers working had been denied honorarium by the Department of Higher Education.They pointed out that the Commissioner for Higher Education had communicated to the Joint Director that the funds had been released, but orders were not issued to the treasury on disbursing it.They sought the intervention of the Chief Minister in the issue to ensure immediate release of funds.They said that they would be forced to boycott classes if the funds were not released.R. Durgappa, president of the district unit of the Karnataka Government College Guest Lecturers Association, was present.